, Hi [~jlowe], can you help take a look please? , Thanks for the report and patch!

Are we sure it's safe to unblock the Nodemanager's async dispatcher during this reboot?  I'm worried that other events could be dispatched to subsystems while they are trying to reset and cause other problems.  I think it would be simpler and safer to have NodeManager#resyncWithRM check a "resyncing" boolean when it's called, avoiding redundantly resyncing if it is currently resyncing.  No need for separate threads and atomic booleans.
, Hi [~jlowe], I am actually not changing this behavior (not to block dispatcher for resync), existing code has been creating a new thread for it. I think the reason is that resync involves draining existing heartbeat thread and a register call to RM, which can take a long time (say network slow or RM is down during master-slave switch). We don't want to block the entire NM for this. It maybe much more involved if we want to change this behavior. , Ah, sorry, I missed that there was a thread earlier as well.  Should have used {{diff -b}} after applying the patch. ;-)

Since the AtomicBoolean is referred to as a lock, I'd like to see it treated as such where the release of it is in a {{finally}} block so it's always released even if exceptions occur.  Otherwise looks good.
